<paragraph id="8BB936ADFFC7F80C53AA2220FC88ABF2" blockId="3.[162,1070,1086,1431]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142">
C o m p a r a t i v e n o t e s: 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D2EFFC7F80C510D2220FCAAAA36" authority="Zettel, 2021" authorityName="Zettel" authorityYear="2021" box="[517,772,1086,1107]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelocheiridae" genus="Aphelocheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aschalewi" status="nov.sp.">
<emphasis id="B972EABFFFC7F80C510D2220FCAAAA36" box="[517,772,1086,1107]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142">Aphelocheirus aschalewi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24157C4FFC7F80C50052220FCF8AA36" box="[781,854,1086,1107]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142" rank="species">nov.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be easily distinguished from its African congeners by small size and a highly contrasting colour pattern (
<figureCitation id="133D2A28FFC7F80C53A22266FF46AAEA" box="[170,232,1144,1167]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[163,196,1390,1412]" captionTargetBox="[163,1069,207,1381]" captionTargetId="figure-72@2.[163,1069,207,1381]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1: Aphelocheirus aschalewi nov.sp., habitus of brachypterous male (holotype); legs omitted." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5275120" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5275120/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D2EFFC7F80C52082266FE70AAE8" authorityName="KIRITSHENKO" authorityYear="1925" box="[256,478,1144,1165]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelocheiridae" genus="Aphelocheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="debilis">
<emphasis id="B972EABFFFC7F80C52082266FE70AAE8" box="[256,478,1144,1165]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142">Aphelocheirus debilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D2EFFC7F80C511C2267FD36AAE8" authorityName="LINNAVUORI" authorityYear="1975" box="[532,664,1144,1166]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelocheiridae" genus="Aphelocheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kumbanus">
<emphasis id="B972EABFFFC7F80C511C2267FD36AAE8" box="[532,664,1144,1166]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142">A. kumbanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, both only known in the macropterous female, possess a more strongly produced forehead (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EF974B5CFFC7F80C51E12288FC06AAC9" author="LINNAVUORI R" box="[745,936,1174,1196]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142" pagination="89 - 91" refId="ref1977" refString="LINNAVUORI R. (1975): On the genus Aphelochirus (Heteroptera, Naucoridae) of tropical Africa. - Notulae e ntomologicae 55: 89 - 91." type="journal article" year="1975">LINNAVUORI 1975</bibRefCitation>
: figs 2a, 3a). Experience with Asian species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D2EFFC7F80C510822ADFD3CAAAD" authorityName="Zettel" authorityYear="2021" box="[512,658,1203,1224]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelocheiridae" genus="Aphelocheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B972EABFFFC7F80C510822ADFD3CAAAD" box="[512,658,1203,1224]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142">Aphelocheirus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has shown that the head shape does not vary among wing morphs of the same species. The forewing remnants of 
<emphasis id="B972EABFFFC7F80C509F22CFFB83AA80" box="[919,1069,1232,1254]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142">A. schoudeteni</emphasis>
are very small, elongate and widely distant from each other (
<bibRefCitation id="EF974B5CFFC7F80C501B22F0FC7CAB61" author="LINNAVUORI R" box="[787,978,1262,1284]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142" pagination="89 - 91" refId="ref1977" refString="LINNAVUORI R. (1975): On the genus Aphelochirus (Heteroptera, Naucoridae) of tropical Africa. - Notulae e ntomologicae 55: 89 - 91." type="journal article" year="1975">LINNAVUORI 1975</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 1a), while those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D2EFFC7F80C52482315FE08AB45" authorityName="POISSON" authorityYear="1955" box="[320,422,1291,1312]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelocheiridae" genus="Aphelocheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="corbeti">
<emphasis id="B972EABFFFC7F80C52482315FE08AB45" box="[320,422,1291,1312]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142">A. corbeti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
meet each other at body midline (
<bibRefCitation id="EF974B5CFFC7F80C50022315FC0EAB44" author="POISSON R" box="[778,928,1291,1313]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142" pagination="154 - 170" refId="ref2042" refString="POISSON R. (1955): Sur quelques Hemipteres aquatiques de l'Afrique orientale et descriptions d'especes nouvelles. - Annali del Museo civico di storia natura le Giacomo Doria 68: 154 - 170." type="journal article" year="1955">POISSON 1955</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 13). The size of the forewings is intermediate in 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D2EFFC7F80C51392337FD1FAB58" authority="Zettel, 2021" authorityName="Zettel" authorityYear="2021" box="[561,689,1320,1342]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelocheiridae" genus="Aphelocheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aschalewi" status="nov.sp.">
<emphasis id="B972EABFFFC7F80C51392337FD1FAB58" box="[561,689,1320,1342]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142">A. aschalewi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24157C4FFC7F80C51B02337FCAFAB5B" box="[696,769,1321,1342]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142" rank="species">nov.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
The genitalia of 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D2EFFC7F80C50A52337FB83AB58" authority="Zettel, 2021" authorityName="Zettel" authorityYear="2021" box="[941,1069,1320,1342]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelocheiridae" genus="Aphelocheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aschalewi" status="nov.sp.">
<emphasis id="B972EABFFFC7F80C50A52337FB83AB58" box="[941,1069,1320,1342]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142">A. aschalewi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24157C4FFC7F80C53AB2358FF40AB3E" box="[163,238,1350,1371]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142" rank="species">nov.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, most of all the parameres, resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D2EFFC7F80C51C22358FC81AB3E" authorityName="POISSON" authorityYear="1955" box="[714,815,1350,1371]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelocheiridae" genus="Aphelocheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="corbeti">
<emphasis id="B972EABFFFC7F80C51C22358FC81AB3E" box="[714,815,1350,1371]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142">A. corbeti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, suggesting a close relationship, however, the apices of both parameres are broader in 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D2EFFC7F80C5020237DFC04AB1D" authority="Zettel, 2021" authorityName="Zettel" authorityYear="2021" box="[808,938,1379,1400]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelocheiridae" genus="Aphelocheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aschalewi" status="nov.sp.">
<emphasis id="B972EABFFFC7F80C5020237DFC04AB1D" box="[808,938,1379,1400]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142">A. aschalewi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24157C4FFC7F80C50BA237AFC55AB1C" box="[946,1019,1380,1401]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142" rank="species">nov.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D2EFFC7F80C53B5239FFE8FABF0" authorityName="POISSON" authorityYear="1955" box="[189,289,1408,1430]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelocheiridae" genus="Aphelocheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="corbeti">
<emphasis id="B972EABFFFC7F80C53B5239FFE8FABF0" box="[189,289,1408,1430]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142">A. corbeti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(comp. 
<figureCitation id="133D2A28FFC7F80C527C239EFE62ABF3" box="[372,460,1408,1430]" captionStart="Figs 2-8" captionStartId="3.[163,203,967,989]" captionTargetBox="[166,1071,369,942]" captionTargetId="figure-342@3.[165,1076,369,942]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 2-8: Aphelocheirus aschalewi nov.sp.: (2) mesosternum, lateral view; (3) apex of propleuron, ventral view; (4) parandria and aedeagus, dorsal view; (5, 6) right paramere in dorsal (5) and approximately ventral view (6); (7, 8) left paramere in dorsal (7) and ventral view (8)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5275122" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5275122/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142">Figs 5–8</figureCitation>
with 
<bibRefCitation id="EF974B5CFFC7F80C510E239FFD37ABF3" author="POISSON R" box="[518,665,1408,1430]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142" pagination="154 - 170" refId="ref2042" refString="POISSON R. (1955): Sur quelques Hemipteres aquatiques de l'Afrique orientale et descriptions d'especes nouvelles. - Annali del Museo civico di storia natura le Giacomo Doria 68: 154 - 170." type="journal article" year="1955">POISSON 1955</bibRefCitation>
: figs 13B, C).
</paragraph>
